HI6UAK8P","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec6lIETVvqT6FF3x","target":"rec6CMR83y25xqFji","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec6lIETVvqT6FF3x","target":"recGpBzggp7LyILNR","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recnY6qGjAJpOOOlf","ref":"John.5.1","text":"After this there was a feast of the Jews; and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.","year":31},{"id":"recRhyJvKxtgnor6b","ref":"John.5.2","text":"Now there is at Jerusalem by the sheep market a pool, which is called in the Hebrew tongue Bethesda, having five porches.","year":31},{"id":"recR9PHK7MbFUR05H","ref":"John.5.3","text":"In these lay a great multitude of impotent folk, of blind, halt, withered, waiting for the moving of the water.","year":31},{"id":"recsdh4CMMXlLgLK4","ref":"John.5.4","text":"For an angel went down at a certain season into the pool, and troubled the water: whosoever then first after the troubling of the water stepped in was made whole of whatsoever disease he had.","year":31},{"id":"recbElsjci8gFGTaC","ref":"John.5.5","text":"And a certain man was there, which had an infirmity thirty and eight years.","year":31},{"id":"recZMPPDdQv0J9WXP","ref":"John.5.6","text":"When Jesus saw him lie, and knew that he had been now a long time in that case, he saith unto him, Wilt thou be made whole?","year":31},{"id":"recDT8Ejnv7Ihpui1","ref":"John.5.7","text":"The impotent man answered him, Sir, I have no man, when the water is troubled, to put me into the pool: but while I am coming, another steppeth down before me.","year":31},{"id":"reclFVnJaBT9HU6AZ","ref":"John.5.8","text":"Jesus saith unto him, Rise, take up thy bed, and walk.","year":31}]}
